$ PowerShell cmdLet get-location

`get-location` returns the current location of the current → Windows/PowerShell/language/provider/drive[drive]. Thus, if the drive is a file system, it returns the *current directory*.

The type of the returned object is a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/PathInfo[`System.Management.Automation.PathInfo`]

{ Aliases

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/alias[Aliases] for `get-location` are `pwd` (which is also a → Linux/shell/commands/pwd[Unix shell command] and stands for *print working directory* ) and `gl`

  Compare the `pwd` alias with the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/pwd[automatic variable `$pwd`].

}

sa:
  → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/location
